.TH DETECT\-CONFLICTS 1 "2026-04-04" "machine-setup 2.0" "Machine Setup Manual"
.SH NAME
detect\-conflicts.sh \- scan for Syncthing conflict files and broken dotfile symlinks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B detect\-conflicts.sh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Scans the dotfiles directory and \fB$HOME\fR for Syncthing conflict files
(files matching the \fB.sync\-conflict\-*\fR pattern) and broken dotfile
symlinks that no longer point to valid targets. Reports findings with
paths and suggested resolutions.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Profile whose dotfile paths should be checked.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
No conflicts or broken symlinks found.
.TP
.B 1
One or more conflicts or broken symlinks detected.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Scan for conflicts using the full profile:
.B detect\-conflicts.sh \-\-profile full
.TP
Quick scan with short option:
.B detect\-conflicts.sh \-p minimal
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR setup.sh (1),
.BR syncthing (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Machine Setup contributors.
